3: 10%

Options 1: 2%, 2: 3%, and 3: 10% are more realistic flow rates for Type1 inlay wax at a 45-degree angle. I would consider factors such as the specific properties of the wax and the complexity of the restoration being created to determine the most appropriate flow rate.

I would ultimately choose the flow rate that allows for the most accurate and precise manipulation of the wax in order to create the desired dental restoration.
